Conestoga Capital Advisors, LLC Bought A Little More Neogen Corporation (NEOG) Stock
July 21, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Neogen Corporation (NASDAQ:NEOG). 
 Conestoga Capital Advisors, LLC reports that it raised its ownership in Neogen Corporation stock by 53,551 shares in its quarterly SEC filing.  Its investment stood at $55,123,000 an increase of $6,350,000 as of the end of the quarter. 
 Conestoga Capital Advisors, LLC isn’t the only one who has changed their investment in NEOG.   As of the end of the quarter Bb&t Corp had disposed of 135 shares trimming its position 2.6%. The value of the company’s investment in Neogen Corporation increased from $339,000 to $348,000 a change of 2.7% quarter to quarter. Aperio Group, LLC grew its stake by buying 860 shares an increase of 5.5% as of 06/30/2017. Aperio Group, LLC now holds 16,610 shares with a value of $1,148,000. The value of the position overall is up by 11.2%.
 As of quarter end Legato Capital Management LLC had bought  a total of 6,242 shares growing its stake by 890.4%. The value of the total investment in Neogen Corporation went from $46,000 to $480,000 increasing 943.5% quarter over quarter.
  On July 14 analysts at CL King began coverage setting a rating of “Neutral”. On December 22 the company was set at “Hold” in a report from Craig-Hallum down from the previous “Buy” rating.





 On March 17 the company was downgraded from “Overweight” to “Equalweight” in a statement from Stephens & Co.. Cowen & Company began coverage of NEOG with a rating of “” and price target of $39.00.
 The company is unchanged by 0.00% since yesterday’s close of $67.53.  Shares of the company are trading at $67.53 which is marginally over $67.43, the stock’s 50 day moving average and which is marginally higher than the 200 day moving average of $64.85.  The 50 day moving average was up $0.10 and the 200 day average moved up $2.68. 
 Neogen Corporation’s P/E ratio is 62.53 and market cap is 2.57B.  As of the last earnings report the EPS was $1.08 and is estimated to be $1.30 for the current year with 38,119,000 shares now outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is forecasted to be $0.33 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $1.45. 
 Short traders are feeling a little more bearish on shares of the company recently if you put credence in the increase in short interest.  The stock experienced a rise in short interest from June 15, 2017 to May 31, 2017 of 1.47%.  Short shares grew 13,729 over that timeframe.  With short interest at 950,855 and short average daily volume at 86,837, days to cover is 10.9 and the percentage of shorted shares was 0.02% on May 31.






